      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LINKIN PARK (7) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2 lengths at Bulli in a handy 22.47 beating Ultimate Sin. Draws out wide but likes the trip. Can measure up again. DIG DEEP RUPEE (5) box seated early before forging to the lead turning and lifting to score (19.57) at Bulli in a Grade 5 over 340m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to her credit. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. JEREMY'S BRIGADE (1) is having his first look at this track. In the money last start when third (30.25) at Gosford over 515m. Boasts three wins from five starts out of this box. Must be included in calculations. FIRST TRAIN OUT (6) missed when well in commission last time but a better run is on the cards.",
